### 9. Hardcoded Port (Minor)

The port `3000` is hardcoded. In production, this should come from an environment variable:

```js
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
});
```

